metadata.ceo: Ms. Claire  Mazumdar Clemon M.B.A., Ph.D.
metadata.description: Bicara Therapeutics Inc., a clinical-stage biopharmaceutical company, develops bifunctional therapies for solid tumors. Its lead program is ficerafusp alfa, a bifunctional antibody that combines an epidermal growth factor receptor (EGFR) directed monoclonal antibody with a domain that binds to human transforming growth factor beta (TGF-b) for the treatment of solid tumors. The company was incorporated in 2018 and is based in Boston, Massachusetts. Bicara Therapeutics Inc. is a subsidiary of Biocon Limited.
